cs.NI, cs.RO, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MA 

This paper involves the placement of unmanned aerial vehicle mounted base stations (UAV-BSs) to prolong the life-time of mobile ad hoc networks. It considers the on-board circuit consumption power and optimal placement to minimize the UAV-recall-frequency (UAV-RF). Therefore, it is likely to belong to the following arXiv CS sub-categories: 

- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): This paper involves the placement of UAV-BSs to improve the performance of mobile ad hoc networks, which is a networking topic. 
- cs.RO (Robotics): The use of UAVs as base stations is a robotics application, and the paper discusses the optimal placement of these UAVs. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper considers the on-board circuit consumption power and optimal placement to minimize the UAV-recall-frequency, which involves information theory concepts. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses the optimal placement of UAV-BSs to improve the performance of mobile ad hoc networks, which is a control problem. 
- cs.MA (Multiagent Systems): The paper involves the placement of UAV-BSs to improve the performance of mobile ad hoc networks, which can be considered a multiagent system.
